The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Aztec Software and Technology Services has posted a net profit of Rs 9.96 crore for the third quarter ended December 31. Revenue during the quarter was at Rs 52.98 crore on consolidated basis, reflecting a 10.67 per cent increase from Rs 48.01 crore in the previous quarter. On a year-on year basis, the revenue growth was 107 per cent higher, while the company?s after-tax profit during the period grew 114 per cent. 

 TV-18 Network has posted a 47 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 12 crore for the quarter ended December 31. Its revenues grew 55 per cent at Rs 38.11 crore for the quarter. The operating profit increased by 54 per cent year-on-year at Rs 20.83 crore.

 Adhunik Metaliks will make an initial public offering to mop up Rs 100 crore from the market. The company has filed the draft Red Herring prospectus with the Securities amp; Exchange Board of India. The shares, with a face value of Rs 10 each, will be sold at a premium. 

 Nipuna Services, Satyam?s BPO subsidiary, has signed a deal with 4K Animation of Germany for various animation projects. The deal is worth 7 million euros. Nipuna will work with the German company on animation projects for a Hollywood film, a TV production and commercials.

 Steel Authority of India has decided to spend Rs 1.5 crore to support preservation of five national monuments at Lodhi Gardens in New Delhi. SAIL has signed an MoU with Archaeological Survey of India and National Culture Fund for this. 

 ION Exchange Asia Pacific, ION?s subsidiary in Singapore, has entered into a joint venture agreement with American Dynamics Holdings. The joint venture will undertake the business of water treatment equipment, ION Exchange has informed the stock exchanges.

 Icra has assigned ?LAAA? rating to the Rs 200-crore bonds of State Bank of Saurashtra. The agency has also assigned ?A1+? rating to the Rs 1,000-crore certficate of deposit of the bank. The ratings took into account the bank?s strong ownership by the State Bank of India and the operating synergies that it has with its parent.

 SKF India has launched SKF Grease for automotive after market customers. The product is available in 0.5 kg, 1 kg, 2 kg, 3 kg and 5 kg packing. The price ranges between Rs 73 and Rs 653. 

 Cummins Auto Services has entered into a strategic alliance with Lexia Motors for providing engines for the latter?s luxury buses.

